First tutorial. So....



[font=Verdana]I'M BAGEL ON R-S!![/font]

Okay, I thought to myself, does any server thats 508 have books that change your magic tab? So I made it.


Open up ItemSelecet.java - in... rs2/io/packets.


Put these cases in there somewhere.

[CODE]case 6767: //Book
p.requestAnim(5864, 0);
p.frames.setTab(p, 79, 192);
p.frames.sendMessage(p, "You converted back to Modern Magic.(MADE BY Bagel)");
break;
case 9003: //Book
p.requestAnim(5864, 0);
p.frames.setTab(p, 79, 193);
p.frames.sendMessage(p, "You converted back Ancient Magic.(MADE BY Bagel)");
break;
case 13151: //Book
p.requestAnim(5864, 0);
p.frames.setTab(p, 79, 430);
p.frames.sendMessage(p, "You converted back Lunar Magic.(MADE BY Bagel)");
break;[/CODE]



Heres a command that I just made to get the books. <-- put in Commands.java. [duh.]

[CODE]if(cmd[0].equals("books")) {
Engine.playerItems.addItem(p, 6767, 1); 
Engine.playerItems.addItem(p, 9003, 1);  
Engine.playerItems.addItem(p, 13151, 1); 
p.frames.sendMessage(p, "Combat book = Lunar. Security book = Ancients. Book = Modern.");   
}[/CODE]

What it does: It changes the magic tab to Modern Magic Tab, Lunar Magic Tab, Ancients Magic Tab by clicking 'Read' on it. :)

Combat book = Lunar.
Security book = Ancients.
Book = Modern.

